    pearls: ["In children with new-onset polyuria and weight loss, always check blood glucose — DKA is the presenting feature in 25–40% of new type 1 DM diagnoses","Hypoglycemia in elderly may present as confusion, falls, or behavioral changes rather than classic tremor and sweating — low threshold for glucose check","Women with gestational diabetes have a 50% lifetime risk of developing type 2 DM — postpartum screening and lifestyle modification are essential","The dawn phenomenon vs. Somogyi effect: dawn phenomenon is from overnight growth hormone; Somogyi is rebound hyperglycemia from nocturnal hypoglycemia — check 2–3 AM glucose to differentiate","Never skip meals while on insulin or sulfonylureas — highest-yield NCLEX safety concept for diabetes"],
